4jh.title: Prime order groups are cyclic
4jh.clickbait: This is the first step on the road to classifying the finite groups.
4jh.text:
Let $G$ be a [-3gd] whose [3gg order] is equal to $p$, a [-4mf].
Then $G$ is [49x isomorphic] to the [-47y] $C_p$ of order $p$.

# Proof
Pick any non-identity element $g$ of the group.

By [4jn Lagrange's theorem], the subgroup generated by $g$ has size $1$ or $p$ (since $p$ was prime).
But it can't be $1$ because the only subgroup of size $1$ is the trivial subgroup.

Hence the subgroup must be the entire group.
